article.headline: Colorado 62, San Francisco 56
article.story:
BOULDER, Colo. (AP) -- Kara Richards scored 22 points to lead
Colorado to a 62-56 season-opening win over San Francisco on Friday
night.

Colorado forward Jackie McFarland added 17 points and grabbed 12
rebounds.

The Dons (0-1) were led in scoring by Dominique Carter, who
scored 22 points. Nickie Warren had 11 points.

The Buffs (1-0) trailed 30-26 at intermission but rallied to
break a 26-game losing streak when trailing at the break and their
first such win since beating Missouri 56-51 on Jan. 18, 2005. The
Buffs trailed the Tigers 28-20 in that game.

Leading 51-49 with 5:10 minutes remaining, the Buffs went on a
9-0 run to pull away for the victory.

Colorado hosts No. 16 Vanderbilt on Sunday.
